Unless you are OK with being forced to use Facebook for multiplayer, don't download this App. I assume single-player works fine, but I never got there because I wanted to play with my kids and this was not possible because of the forced Facebook integration. We LOVED the game "clue" by the same studio. The experience of multiplayer gameplay with the family was great, because it worked like Kahoot you enter a lobby with a code everybody else enters a code and it just works. For this one it seems like you have to use Facebook as the mechanism for inviting other people. Out of my family of four two of us had to completely uninstall and reinstall the game and we could never even get a single game to launch. Wish it worked. Plus our kids don't have Facebook. We temporarily created accounts (had to use incorrect birthdates), just to get them to be able to see the invitation. This was very disappointing, especially considering how great "Clue" was. Why would Marmalade Studios create two completely different login/collaboration flows? More to the point, why would they think it's a good idea to require me to use Facebook? I assume they're getting a significant kickback from Facebook for driving users through the FB platform. This was a terrible choice IMO.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback. The Game of Life is our oldest game and, at the time, Facebook was our only option for a multiplayer system. We have since grown, and now make sure to always implement a lobby-code system in our games. Since you were unaware of this fact, we would be happy to assist you with a refund.Contact us at help@marmalademail.com

I've always loved The Game of Life. This app does pretty well with it. I 
love all the avatars and themed boards you can purchase. However, part of 
the fun of the game is to be able to see your LIFE as you're creating it. 
You are unable to check what your job is unless you can remember from the 
tiny picture inside your info box. You can't check what you earn, what your 
lucky number earns, or even what kind of house you bought. This is very 
unhelpful when trying to decide if you want to change careers or buy a 
house. If you have more than four kids, they won't fit into your minivan. 
They just disappear, only remembered at the scorecard in the end. You can't 
check the map when at a stop sign; I'd like to see what each path is like 
before choosing. Too many Life cards repeat themselves in one game. 
Finally, there are no regular life spaces like in the original game! If you 
were an accountant and someone landed on a space to pay taxes with your 
accountant $ symbol, they paid you! Same for doctors on a red cross 
payment, etc. Best of all, if you WERE the accountant or doctor, you don't 
pay! The board game was better, but I think if the developers start keeping 
it truer to the board game, it will be amazing! Regardless of all my 
suggestions, this game is really fun! Hoping to change my rating to 5 stars 
soon! ☺

Based on the current Hasbro edition, this mobile adaptation of The Game of Life manages to hit all the right aesthetic notes. The spinner, the cars, the pegs, the buildings, and the long yellow track are all here. It's a shame Hasbro has oversimplified the game for modern players, because without the dynamic of playing against a table of friends/family...the digital version can feel very repetitive & drawn out. Fortunately, Marmalade has given us a Fast Forward button, so we can fly through AI moves & avoid the crushing tedium of watching a computer have all the fun.  A wide variety of themed boards & playing pieces are available as IAPs. Some of them are cute visual upgrades (Halloween), and some of them are just random (Birthday Party...?). All of them are entirely unnecessary for enjoying the classic LIFE experience.  The most consistently unresolved issue, however, is how unstable the app really is. I haven't been able to finish an online multiplayer game for months because the app ALWAYS crashes 1/4 of the way into the game. Solo games against AI players have also become unstable, but at least those auto save.   It's also incredibly tedious setting up a new game. Leave the shop content to a shop tab/screen. I don't want to scroll through the dozen or so icons/vehicles I haven't purchased just to find one I have. The vehicle color indicator needs work, too. Sometimes I don't get the warning sign my vehicle is incompatible with a selected color, and I end up with a floating pawn in an invisible car for the whole game.
replyContent:
Hi Samuel,
Thank you so much for your thorough feedback! We’re very happy that you’re enjoying your THE GAME OF LIFE experience. We will take all of your suggestions into account and hope to surprise you with our future updates!
We’d love to hear about any other features you’d like to see in the game.
Thanks again!

The Game of Life requests access to your storage in order to finish the download of the app, which would not be possible unless the installation files could be saved on your device. We don’t view, use or store your data anywhere.
Don't hesitate to contact us at contactus@marmalademail.com .
We apologize for the confusion.

I've always enjoyed this game, ever since I first played it as a board game with my family. This adds some great fun to it. However, when playing pass and play, I would imagine it would be nearly impossible to both play one of the spin games at the same time. On a larger screen like an iPad it wouldn't be quite as bad, but on a smaller smart phone screen? Impossible. Plus, your fingers would get into each other's way. Please consider changing this, so that each player would play the game separately. It would make it much easier. One more thing...the prices for the themes are waaaaay to expensive. I would consider buying one or more if they were 99 cents each, but certainly not at $3.99. I think if they were super cheap, like 10 cents each, I'd buy all of them. It would be even better, however, if you included the themes with the initial purchase price of the game. I know you probably won't be willing to do that, but a price reduction would be an acceptable alternative.

Hi Tk venoms, 
To restore your purchases just press the “Buy” button on the worlds you’ve previously purchased. This forces the game to connect to the Google Play store and unlock the content without charging you again.
Best regards.

Why do I have to land on a space for the opportunity to buy a house!?  This is BS!  I absolutely hate this mechanic!  It means you can go through an entire game...HOMELESS, if you never land on a house space!  Don't get me wrong, it's not all bad. I've said this before but no one seem to care to respond (the company) I don't understand why this game plays like it does it's a very unfair game  1 of my main problems is when you land on the person's lucky number that person gets a lot of money like for example 150 it varies but if they land on your number you get 20 or 50 it varies the other person always get a lot more and the funny thing is I'm playing the other person as well  but now I guess since it updated when you land on your own number you would get the amount that the person would have given you if they landed on it like for example  earlier when I played I got 50 but yet when the other person (myself) landed on the lucky number the other player (Me) would get a whole bunch more like a 150 it varies each game  it seems so crazy  Then at the end of the game when they do the retirement and stuff like that one person would get 3000 and the other person would get 4000   I'm pretty sure again the company that supposedly looks to see what people think about the game isn't going to Care to respond once again or do anything about it  But yet if you have to pay money they're real happy about that but they don't care about fixing the problem that the CUSTOMER  has That's not very BUSINESSLIKE if you ask me.
replyContent:
Hi Shirley,
The reason the lucky number payout differs from player to player is that it is dependent on the Career of that player. If you land on the lucky number of a Film Star they win 20k, but a Teacher would win 90k. These values are shown on the Career Cards when you’re prompted to choose a Career.
We apologize for the confusion.

Hi Jo,
The Game of Life requests access to your storage in order to finish the download of the app, which would not be possible unless the installation files could be saved on your device. We don’t view, use or store your data anywhere.
Don't hesitate to contact us at https://marmaladegamestudio.com/contact-us/ .
We apologize for the confusion.
